text: The L. J. Arthur House is located in Lancaster, Wisconsin. ==History== L. J. Arthur was a local attorney. The house was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1980 and on the State Register of Historic Places in 1989. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:National Register of Historic Places in Grant County, Wisconsin Category:Houses in Grant County, Wisconsin Category:Victorian architecture in Wisconsin Category:Brick buildings and structures Category:Houses completed in 1880
